\title{Linear Least Square Estimation}
\taxon{definition}

\p{
  If the estimator in a LSE estimation is \strong{linear}, then it is called a \strong{Linear Least Square Estimator (LLSE)}.
}

\p{
  The LLSE of #{Y} given #{X}, denoted by #{L [Y \mid X] } is the linear function #{a + b X} that minimizes the mean square error #{E[(Y - a - b X)^2]}.

  ##{
    L [Y \mid X] = E[Y] + \frac{\operatorname{Cov}(X, Y)}{\operatorname{Var}(X)} (X - E[X])
  }
}
